Elk Rapids is a small town in Michigan, so there aren't a ton of restaurants to choose from, but there are definitely some good options. Here are a few restaurants in Elk Rapids that are highly rated by customers:

Siren Hall - A seafood restaurant with a modern atmosphere and creative menu featuring fresh fish, shellfish, and other seafood dishes. They also offer a selection of craft beers and cocktails.

Pearl's New Orleans Kitchen - A Cajun and Creole restaurant that serves authentic Louisiana-style dishes, including gumbo, jambalaya, and po'boys. They also have a full bar with a selection of cocktails, beer, and wine.

Java Jones - A cozy coffee shop and cafe that serves coffee, tea, baked goods, breakfast sandwiches, and light lunch fare. They also offer free Wi-Fi and have outdoor seating available.

Elk Rapids Pizza - A casual pizza joint that serves a variety of classic and specialty pizzas, as well as salads, sandwiches, and appetizers. They also offer gluten-free crust options.

Town Club - A historic restaurant and bar that has been a fixture in Elk Rapids since 1929. They serve classic American dishes, such as burgers, steaks, and sandwiches, and have a full bar with a selection of beer, wine, and cocktails.